{
  "stem": "15686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was no country in the world that would take Jews without a long waiting period, without having a visa, without having a lot of people in that country that would vouch, say, for them and sponsor them and what have you.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was one place in the world that Jews could go to without any paper.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All they needed was a ticket, and that was China, the city of Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The city of Shanghai in 1939 was already occupied by the Japanese, and apparently the Japanese had established some ammunition factories in Shanghai, but they could not get enough labor to work them.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they let Jews in, and they put them in a ghetto in Shanghai, and they them work in the ammunition factories.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All this, of course, I found out much later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at the time, China and Shanghai was a total unknown to everyone, because in Germany I had never seen a Chinese person.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I don't know if my parents ever had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my father and my mother scraped together some money very quickly-- sold some jewelry and things-- and bought-- had enough to buy two tickets on a ship that left Germany the next day to go to China.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they decided that we were going to Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother now had to make a terrible decision, because she didn't know what she should do with my brother and myself.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was 13, my brother was 12.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- she could have borrowed enough money to buy two additional tickets to go to China with them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But on the other hand, she said I don't know what China is.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know what they're going to do to us there.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
